UPDATE public.job_postings
  SET description = $desc$<p><strong>WHO WE ARE</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>ActBlue is a nonprofit organization dedicated to creating cutting-edge technology that fuels Democratic victories and enables progressive causes to thrive.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Our vision is simple: building change through the power of people. Since our founding, we’ve been building innovative solutions to revolutionize grassroots fundraising – if you’ve donated to a Democratic campaign or a progressive organization online, you’ve probably used our platform! We believe in putting power in the hands of small-dollar donors by helping thousands of groups — from local candidates to national movements — mobilize their communities and create a lasting impact. Every member of our team is deeply committed to advancing our shared mission and core values. Together, we are shaping the future of democracy.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>THE OPPORTUNITY</strong></p>
<p>The People &amp; Culture team aims to establish ActBlue as a top employer of choice for people who are passionate about empowering small-dollar donors in our country. We attract diverse, talented employees and promote an engaging, inclusive culture where team members develop, thrive and catalyze positive change.&nbsp;</p>
<p>As a People &amp; Culture (P&amp;C) Initiatives Partner at ActBlue, you will play a pivotal role working closely with multiple teams and leaders across our business to drive the development and impact of the P&amp;C organization. You will serve as a full strategic partner to the Chief P&amp;C Officer and P&amp;C leadership team. As the Partner, you will provide leadership to the strategy development and planning process, will define and deliver executive communications and will implement new programmatic P&amp;C strategic initiatives. Additionally, you will be relied on to provide thought leadership, drive value-creating insights, and influence the growth and trajectory of the P&amp;C organization. In this role, you'll have exposure to the leadership team and P&amp;C, while also being engaged in the core operating rhythms that touch all employees.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The P&amp;C Initiatives Partner is an integral member of ActBlue’s People &amp; Culture team, will act as a trusted advisor to leaders and staff, and will report to the Chief P&amp;C Officer.</p>
<p><strong>WHAT YOU WILL DO</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Partner with the Chief P&amp;C Officer and the P&amp;C Leadership team to accelerate long-term goals, planning and operations</li>
<li>Collaborate with Chief P&amp;C Officer on P&amp;C and organizational strategy and goal setting</li>
<li>Operate as proxy for Chief P&amp;C Officer in P&amp;C operations not requiring her direct engagement.</li>
<li>Drive collaboration across P&amp;C teams to maximize efficiency and effectiveness</li>
<li>Work with Chief P&amp;C Officer to prepare leadership presentations and strategy reviews&nbsp;</li>
<li>Prepare and organize all aspects of leadership meetings and presentations, including establishing operating rhythms, working with administrative support staff on scheduling, setting agendas, and driving appropriate follow-up.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Work with P&amp;C Leads on goal and project management and tracking.</li>
<li>Provide high-level support to the Chief P&amp;C Officer, ensuring P&amp;C teams have the full range of data and information to drive effective decision-making</li>
<li>Drive agenda for P&amp;C staff meetings and responsible for driving follow up on action items as well as input to leadership offsites.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Proactively assess P&amp;C org needs, make recommendations, and implement agreed upon solutions</li>
<li>Provide rigorous data analysis and reporting solutions based on business needs</li>
<li>Design and facilitate business team and offsite leadership meetings as needed</li>
<li>May support supplementary projects as assigned, ensuring timely and efficient completion in line with organizational objectives and standards.</li>
</ul>
<p><str$desc$
